comments:
If you set a 3.1.1 JRE on a Java Project, VE fails to bring up a class extending
a jFrame.  It seems to barf on the overrideProperty() in the BeanProxy Adapter
with SF_JFRAME_DEFAULTCLOSEPERATION feature - is was instrospected.
What is a 3.1.1 jre? Do you perhaps mean 1.3.1 JRE?

(In reply to comment #1)
> What is a 3.1.1 jre? Do you perhaps mean 1.3.1 JRE?
Bug appear with JRE 1.4.2_02 and 1.4.2_09 under Win2K. VE just not starting on 
Eclipse's startup with error dewscribed upper.
